President Obama has declared an emergency in Virginia and ordered federal aid to help with the response efforts following the impact of Hurricane Irene. The declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance for emergency measures. The affected areas include several counties and cities in Virginia. FEMA will mobilize equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75% of funding provided by the federal government. Donald L. Keldsen has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For further information, media can contact the FEMA news desk.